<bibRefCitation id="EF884B68FFA7FFC2FF5AFF5540C6E3E6" author="Mentz and de Oliveira" box="[159,503,218,240]" firstAuthor="Mentz" journalOrPublisher="Pesquisas" pageId="9" pageNumber="479" pagination="1 - 327" part="54" refId="ref29633" refString="Mentz, L. A. and P. L. de Oliveira. 2004. Solanum (Solanaceae) no regiao sul do Brasil. Pesquisas 54: 1 - 327." title="Solanum (Solanaceae) no regiao sul do Brasil" type="journal article" year="2004">Mentz and de Oliveira (2004)</bibRefCitation>
also placed specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="4C194D1AFFA7FFC2FF5AFF764017E21A" box="[159,294,247,269]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="9" pageNumber="479" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="adscendens">
<emphasis id="B96DEA8BFFA7FFC2FF5AFF764017E21A" box="[159,294,247,269]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="479">S. adscendens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<emphasis id="B96DEA8BFFA7FFC2FE99FF7640D3E21A" box="[348,482,247,269]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="479">S. olympicum</emphasis>
together in 
<taxonomicName id="4C194D1AFFA7FFC2FDA1FF7643DBE21A" box="[612,746,247,269]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="9" pageNumber="479" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="adscendens">
<emphasis id="B96DEA8BFFA7FFC2FDA1FF7643DBE21A" box="[612,746,247,269]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="479">S. adscendens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. This placement was largely due to the absence of type material, as the presumed holotype was destroyed in Berlin and the photographs of it were not sufficient to distinguish the species. 
<bibRefCitation id="EF884B68FFA7FFC2FF38FEE3436BE294" author="Mentz and de Oliveira's" box="[253,602,364,386]" firstAuthor="Mentz" journalOrPublisher="Pesquisas" pageId="9" pageNumber="479" pagination="1 - 327" part="54" refId="ref29633" refString="Mentz, L. A. and P. L. de Oliveira. 2004. Solanum (Solanaceae) no regiao sul do Brasil. Pesquisas 54: 1 - 327." title="Solanum (Solanaceae) no regiao sul do Brasil" type="journal article" year="2004">Mentz and de Oliveira’s (2004)</bibRefCitation>
photographs of a duplicate of the type at Paris enabled us to readily distinguish 
<taxonomicName id="4C194D1AFFA7FFC2FF27FE294058E2AA" box="[226,361,423,444]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="9" pageNumber="479" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="adscendens">
<emphasis id="B96DEA8BFFA7FFC2FF27FE294058E2AA" box="[226,361,423,444]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="479">S. adscendens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the more common and widespread 
<emphasis id="B96DEA8BFFA7FFC2FF5AFE4A4000E2CF" box="[159,305,452,473]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="479">S. olympicum.</emphasis>
The cordate leaf bases, straight (not geniculate) hairs, glandular hairs on the abaxial leaf surface, and sprawling growth form with many branches from a single base characterize 
<taxonomicName id="4C194D1AFFA7FFC2FE0AFD92436FE127" box="[463,606,540,561]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="9" pageNumber="479" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="adscendens">
<emphasis id="B96DEA8BFFA7FFC2FE0AFD92436FE127" box="[463,606,540,561]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="479">S. adscendens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and differentiate it from 
<emphasis id="B96DEA8BFFA7FFC2FF33FDB740B2E158" box="[246,387,569,590]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="479">S. olympicum</emphasis>
, as do molecular data.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA63699FFA7FFC2FF72FDEC4013E08D" blockId="9.[159,806,610,924]" pageId="9" pageNumber="479">
<taxonomicName id="4C194D1AFFA7FFC2FF72FDEC4312E161" authorityName="Dunal" authorityYear="1852" box="[183,547,610,631]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="9" pageNumber="479" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="amarantoides" variety="hirtellum">
<emphasis id="B96DEA8BFFA7FFC2FF72FDEC40A4E161" box="[183,405,610,631]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="479">Solanum amarantoides</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis id="B96DEA8BFFA7FFC2FE0CFDEC4312E161" box="[457,547,610,631]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="479">hirtellum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has not previously been considered a synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="4C194D1AFFA7FFC2FE11FD0E4354E182" box="[468,613,639,661]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="9" pageNumber="479" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="adscendens">
<emphasis id="B96DEA8BFFA7FFC2FE11FD0E4354E182" box="[468,613,639,661]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="479">S. adscendens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but both Bitter and C.V. Morton annotated the holotype at Pas “affine 
<taxonomicName id="4C194D1AFFA7FFC2FF5AFD34401BE1D9" box="[159,298,698,719]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="9" pageNumber="479" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="adscendens">
<emphasis id="B96DEA8BFFA7FFC2FF5AFD34401BE1D9" box="[159,298,698,719]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="479">S. adscendens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” and “probably = 
<taxonomicName id="4C194D1AFFA7FFC2FE32FD3443B0E1D9" box="[503,641,698,719]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="9" pageNumber="479" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="adscendens">
<emphasis id="B96DEA8BFFA7FFC2FE32FD3443B0E1D9" box="[503,641,698,719]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="479">S. adscendens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
,” respectively. The original printed label indicates the specimen was collected in “Province de Rio-Grande” but unidentified handwriting above this label states “de Minas Geraes.” 
<taxonomicName id="4C194D1AFFA7FFC2FD09FC9F403EE055" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="9" pageNumber="479" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="adscendens">
<emphasis id="B96DEA8BFFA7FFC2FD09FC9F403EE055" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="479">Solanum adscendens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has its northern limit at the border of Rio Grande do Sul and Santa Catarina States, so it is unlikely that the 
<emphasis id="B96DEA8BFFA7FFC2FEC5FCE7409CE068" box="[256,429,873,894]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="479">Gaudichaud 1745</emphasis>
specimen was collected in Minas Gerais State.
</paragraph>
